"2017-07-27T10:19:11.252Z","comments_closed?":false,"facebook_team?":false,"team_private?":false,"vulnerability_information":"We tested the Android app, v2.0.2\n\nTo replicate:\n\n    Install the app, and run it until you reach the login screen.\n\n    Install PacketCapture:\n    https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=app.greyshirts.sslcapture\n\n    Go to PacketCapture, go through setup, SKIP the SSL certificate\n    install process\n\n    Activate PacketCapture At this point all network traffic will be\n    going through PacketCapture. SSL traffic will be encrypted using a\n    self-signed certificate, not trusted by the device.\n\n    Go back to to the app, enter any credentials and try to login.\n\n    In PacketCapture, observe login calls without any SSL being used\n\nYou can also replicate this issue with an MITM proxy\n\nImplications is that anybody monitoring the network can see the login credentials","vulnerability_information_html":"\u003cp\u003eWe tested the Android app, v2.0.2\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eTo replicate:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"highlight\"\u003e\u003cpre class=\"highlight plaintext\"\u003e\u003ccode\u003eInstall the app, and run it until you reach the login screen.\n\nInstall PacketCapture:\nhttps://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=app.greyshirts.sslcapture\n\nGo to PacketCapture, go through setup, SKIP the SSL certificate\ninstall process\n\nActivate PacketCapture At this point all network traffic will be\ngoing through PacketCapture. SSL traffic will be encrypted using a\nself-signed certificate, not trusted by the device.\n\nGo back to to the app, enter any credentials and try to login.\n\nIn PacketCapture, observe login calls without any SSL being used\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou can also replicate this issue with an MITM proxy\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eImplications is that anybody monitoring the network can see the login credentials\u003c/p\u003e\n","weakness":{"id":32